==Translingual==
===Etymology===
Derived from the [[Phoenician]] letter [[aleph]] [[Image:phoenician_aleph.png|20px|Aleph]].

===Symbol===
'''Α'''
# The [[upper case]] letter [[alpha]], the first letter of the modern [[Greek alphabet]].

'''Α''''
# The number one in [[Greek numeral]]s.

''',Α'''
# The number 1000 in Greek numerals.

==={{Initialism}}===
'''Α'''
# '''[[ανατολικός]]''' (east)


===Pronunciation===
* In modern Greek it represents the [[w:Open front unrounded vowel|[a]]] sound similar to the '''a''' in ''h'''a'''t'' and '''''A'''thens''.
* [[IPA]] /æ/ /ə/
* [[SAMPA]] /{/ /@/

